WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.853
<v Jamie>Jamie here, and Oracle just jumped six point four seven percent on their earnings beat, what's behind this move, Alex?

00:00:06.853 --> 00:00:20.903
<v Alex>Alex on equities, the earnings report showed a significant increase in cloud revenue, which is driving the stock price up, but let's not forget that the company still has a lot of work to do to catch up with its competitors.

00:00:20.903 --> 00:00:26.043
<v Jamie>Right, exactly, and what about the broader market, Cam, any reactions to the earnings reports?

00:00:26.043 --> 00:00:37.352
<v Cam>Cam on macro, the market seems to be shrugging off the earnings reports for now, but we're seeing some movement in the bond market, with the ten-year treasury yield down twenty-seven basis points.

00:00:37.352 --> 00:00:47.632
<v Maya>Maya from tech, and I think the real story here is the growth in cloud revenue, we're seeing a huge shift towards cloud computing, and Oracle is benefiting from that.

00:00:47.632 --> 00:00:54.486
<v Kai>Kai with a question, doesn't this mean that Oracle is finally catching up with the likes of Amazon and Microsoft?

00:00:54.486 --> 00:01:02.025
<v Maya>Yes, exactly, and it's not just Oracle, we're seeing a lot of other companies making big moves in the cloud space.

00:01:02.025 --> 00:01:08.193
<v Jamie>Okay, let's not get ahead of ourselves, but what about the other big earners, Alex, any surprises?

00:01:08.193 --> 00:01:20.187
<v Alex>Well, Salesforce is up four point one three percent, and Apple is up three point two four percent, but the real surprise is Gildan, which is up seventy-seven percent after UBS upgraded the stock.

00:01:20.187 --> 00:01:33.551
<v Tess>Tess at retail, and I think this is a great example of how a strong earnings report can really move the needle for a company, but we also need to look at the bigger picture, what's driving consumer spending?

00:01:33.551 --> 00:01:42.461
<v Cam>Consumer spending is still a big question mark, with the dollar index up thirteen basis points, it's hard to say what's going to happen next.

00:01:42.461 --> 00:01:51.370
<v Dev>Dev on crypto, and I think it's interesting to note that Bitcoin is only up sixteen basis points, despite all the excitement around the earnings reports.

00:01:51.370 --> 00:01:55.825
<v Kai>Yeah, because nothing says excitement like a sixteen basis point move, right?

00:01:55.825 --> 00:01:59.937
<v Maya>Hey, don't knock it, Kai, every little bit counts in crypto.

00:01:59.937 --> 00:02:08.847
<v Rio>Rio checking in, and I think we need to look at the global picture, what's happening in other markets, and how that's affecting the US market.

00:02:08.847 --> 00:02:13.645
<v Jamie>Right, exactly, and what about the Iran peace proposal, Rio, any updates on that?

00:02:13.645 --> 00:02:22.554
<v Rio>Yes, it seems like the US has responded to the proposal, but we're still waiting for confirmation, and the situation is still very fluid.

00:02:22.554 --> 00:02:26.324
<v Alex>Because nothing says fluid situation like a peace proposal, right?

00:02:26.324 --> 00:02:27.694
<v Kai>Oh, burn, Alex.

00:02:27.694 --> 00:02:34.205
<v Maya>Okay, okay, let's not get too distracted, what about the other big news, like the Foxconn satellite launch?

00:02:34.205 --> 00:02:36.947
<v Jamie>Yeah, what's the deal with that, Maya?

00:02:36.947 --> 00:02:45.857
<v Maya>Well, Foxconn just launched two new satellites, and it's a big deal for the company, they're trying to expand their reach into the space industry.

00:02:45.857 --> 00:02:50.311
<v Tess>Because what every company needs is a side hustle in space, right?

00:02:50.311 --> 00:02:54.081
<v Cam>Hey, don't knock it, Tess, space is the new frontier.

00:02:54.081 --> 00:02:58.536
<v Kai>Yeah, and who knows, maybe we'll see a space-based Oracle cloud soon.

00:02:58.536 --> 00:03:02.648
<v Dev>Yeah, because that's exactly what we need, a cloud in space.

00:03:02.648 --> 00:03:08.131
<v Jamie>Okay, okay, let's wrap it up, what's the one thing you're watching this week, Alex?

00:03:08.131 --> 00:03:12.928
<v Alex>I'm watching the bond market, Jamie, it's going to be a wild ride.

00:03:12.928 --> 00:03:18.411
<v Maya>And I'm watching the tech space, there are so many exciting developments happening right now.

00:03:18.411 --> 00:03:23.209
<v Rio>I'm watching the global situation, Jamie, it's a complex and fluid situation.

00:03:23.209 --> 00:03:29.377
<v Kai>And I'm watching for any more satellite launches, maybe we'll see a space-based pizza delivery service next.

00:03:29.377 --> 00:03:34.517
<v Jamie>This show is for entertainment and education only — nothing here is investment advice.
